liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Stuart Broad and the Australians are chirping, the boos are ringing down as the Australian team leave the field, and Usman Khawaja has just stopped to confront a member as he walked through the long room. After days of near silence in the stands, the Lord's fans suddenly sound like a football crowd. The 'Same old Aussies, always cheating' chant is the soundtrack now, and Broad is playing the pantomime villain. There's a risk of this turning ugly, particularly with Broad and the Aussie fielders. And I just realised it could get even worse if Ollie Robinson gets out there. The game will be won and lost in the next session. Pop the kettle on. You can't go to bed now!
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: LUNCH: England 6-243, needing 128 to win (Stokes 108*, Broad 1*)

props.alt: England batter Ben Stokes raises his bat during an Ashes Test at Lord's.

children.content: Stuart Broad and the Australians are chirping, the boos are ringing down as the Australian team leave the field, and Usman Khawaja has just stopped to confront a member as he walked through the long room.

After days of near silence in the stands, the Lord's fans suddenly sound like a football crowd. The 'Same old Aussies, always cheating' chant is the soundtrack now, and Broad is playing the pantomime villain.
There's a risk of this turning ugly, particularly with Broad and the Aussie fielders. And I just realised it could get even worse if Ollie Robinson gets out there.
The game will be won and lost in the next session. Pop the kettle on. You can't go to bed now!

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: The ball was bowled, he ducked, and Carey took it. Then Bairstow just ambled out of his crease and Carey threw down the stumps straight away. Looked like umpire Ahsan Raza was reaching for the bowler's cap, but had he called over? It seems not, and that's given out!! Wow. If Starc's non-catch was controversial, that will be doubly so. Again, correct by the letter of the law, but English fans and players will be less than pleased.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: Bairstow's been run out in outlandish circumstances at the end of the over!
